.TH AXT-DRIFT 1
.SH NAME
axt-drift \- mark filesystem state and report changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axt-drift
[\fIFLAGS\fR] mark [--name \fINAME\fR] [--hash]
.br
.B axt-drift
[\fIFLAGS\fR] diff [--since \fINAME\fR] [--hash]
.br
.B axt-drift
[\fIFLAGS\fR] run [--name \fINAME\fR] [--hash] -- \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARG\fR...]
.br
.B axt-drift
[\fIFLAGS\fR] list
.br
.B axt-drift
[\fIFLAGS\fR] reset
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axt-drift
stores filesystem marks and later reports created, modified, and deleted files.
It is intended for build, generator, CI, and test workflows.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --name \fINAME\fR
Use a named mark. The default name is default.
.TP
.B --since \fINAME\fR
Diff against a named mark.
.TP
.B --hash
Use BLAKE3 content hashes in addition to metadata.
.SH OUTPUT
Supports human, compact, --json, and --agent. Compact text is the non-TTY default. JSON emits schema axt.drift.v1. Agent mode emits summary-first JSONL.
.SH FILES
.I .axt/drift/<name>.jsonl
stores snapshot records. The .axt directory is excluded from snapshots.
.SH EXAMPLES
.EX
axt-drift mark --name before
axt-drift --json diff --since before
axt-drift run -- cargo build
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR axt-run (1),
.BR axt-peek (1)
